en.name: Modify Leave Request
en.shortDesc: Can be able to change the leave dates or can even cancel the request

Flow to allow an employee to request leave days from their employer. Need to collect the date range of the leave, the reason for the leave, and the number of leave days requested. Once the information is collected, make a service call to check for available leave days and inform the employee if there are any issues with the request. If there are no issues, make another service call to submit the request and provide confirmation to the employee.

alternateQuestions.question: What exactly does 'primary caregiver' mean in our context?
In simple terms, what constitutes someone as a primary caregiver?

answer.text: We consider someone the primary caregiver if he or she has primary responsibility for the care of a child immediately following the birth or the coming of the child into the custody, care and control of the parent for the first time. This definition applies to both births and adoptions.

faqs.question: Who do I contact for general on-line W4 questions?

alternateQuestions.question: To whom should I reach out if I have general questions about the online W-4 form?
Could you let me know who I should contact if I require assistance with the online W-4?

faqs.label: Who do I contact for general on-line W4 questions?

answer.text: You can contact the Payroll Help desk at 1-7575 for W4 questions.

faqs.question: How do I print W2 form?

alternateQuestions.question: What are the steps for generating a printed copy of my W-2 form?
Can you explain how to get a paper copy of my W-2 form?

faqs.label: How do I print W2 form?

answer.text: To print W2 form from the HR portal.

faqs.question: When can I expect my annual form W2?

alternateQuestions.question: When is the estimated delivery date for my annual Form W-2?
When can I reasonably expect to have my Form W-2 in my possession?
When will my annual Form W-2 be made available to me?

faqs.label: When can I expect my annual form W2?

answer.text: All employee W2s are mailed on or around January 31st for the prior calendar year.

faqs.question: How do I update my contact information in the employee database?
faqs.label: How do I update my contact information in the employee database?

answer.text: You can typically update your contact information by logging into the employee portal or contacting HR directly.

faqs.question: What is the process for requesting a leave of absence, and what types of leaves are available?
faqs.label: What is the process for requesting a leave of absence, and what types of leaves are available?

answer.text: Companies have specific policies for leaves of absence. Check with HR for details on how to request and the types of leaves offered.

faqs.question: For how long I can take Paid Parental Leave?

alternateQuestions.question: Is there a limit to the length of Paid Parental Leave I can request?

faqs.label: For how long I can take Paid Parental Leave?

answer.text: Paid Parental Leave is designed to provide staff time and financial support to adjust to the addition of a new family member during the important period immediately following the birth or adoption of a child. Staff members are eligible to receive Paid Parental Leave during the first 12 weeks following the birth or adoption of a child. (In order to receive the full paid benefit, a staff member would need to begin his or her leave by the sixth week following a birth or adoption so he or she could take the required three consecutive weeks prior to receiving the three weeks of paid leave).

alternateQuestions.question: What criteria are used to decide who the primary caregiver is?
Can you explain the process for establishing the primary caregiver?

answer.text: The staff member determines who in his or her family is the primary caregiver by signing an affidavit as part of the Paid Parental Leave Request form.

faqs.question: What is the difference between paid leave and unpaid leave?

alternateQuestions.question: What is the difference between unpaid leave and paid leave?

faqs.label: What is the difference between paid leave and unpaid leave?

answer.text: Paid leave refers to time off with regular pay, such as vacation days or paid holidays, while unpaid leave means you are taking time off without pay, often for reasons like personal leave or extended time off.

faqs.question: How do I calculate the amount of leave I have available?
faqs.label: How do I calculate the amount of leave I have available?

answer.text: You can usually check your available leave balance through your company's HR system or by contacting your HR department. It's often based on your accrual rate and previous leave usage.

faqs.question: What happens to unused leave at the end of the year?
faqs.label: What happens to unused leave at the end of the year?

answer.text: Some companies allow you to carry over unused leave to the next year, while others may have a "use it or lose it" policy. Check your company's specific policy.

faqs.question: How do I request a change to my previously approved leave request?
faqs.label: How do I request a change to my previously approved leave request?

answer.text: To request a change to your approved leave, please follow our company's leave change request process, which typically involves contacting your manager or HR department and submitting a formal request.

faqs.question: What is the deadline for requesting changes to leave requests?
faqs.label: What is the deadline for requesting changes to leave requests?

answer.text: The deadline for requesting changes to leave requests varies by company. Please consult your organization's leave policy for specific deadlines.

faqs.question: Is there a limit to the number of times I can change my leave request?
faqs.label: Is there a limit to the number of times I can change my leave request?

answer.text: Company policies may have limitations on the number of times you can change your leave request. It's advisable to review your company's policy for such details.

faqs.question: What should I do if I need to change my leave request due to unforeseen circumstances or an emergency?
faqs.label: What should I do if I need to change my leave request due to unforeseen circumstances or an emergency?

answer.text: In case of unforeseen circumstances or emergencies, contact your manager or HR department as soon as possible to discuss the situation and request a change to your leave.
